OL,3,CMan killed wife before taking own life
OL,4,Cduring psychotic episode, inquest hears
OL,6,FThe Portsmouth inquest heard that Mr
OL,7,FStone-Houghton had suffered a rapid
OL,8,Fdeterioration in his mental health in
OL,9,FApril 2022, after he had been forced
OL,10,Fto close down his jewellery business
OL,11,Fafter it had struggled through the
OL,12,FCovid-19 pandemic.
OL,14,FCoroner Rachel Spearing said that
OL,15,Ffamily and friends became increasingly
OL,16,Fconcerned for him in April and May of
OL,17,Fthat year, because of his "anxious and
OL,18,Fmanic" behaviour, and he was then
OL,19,Fsectioned in June 2022 after he
OL,20,F"violently" self-harmed.
