OL,3,CMan killed wife before taking own life
OL,4,Cduring psychotic episode, inquest hears
OL,6,FShe said: "I accept the evidence of
OL,7,Fall three consultant psychiatrists
OL,8,Fthat on the balance of probabilities
OL,9,Fis it likely that Chris experienced a
OL,10,Ffurther psychotic episode earlier that
OL,11,Fmorning resulting in his actions
OL,12,Ftowards Ruth which ended her life."
OL,14,FRecording a narrative verdict stating
OL,15,Fthat Mrs Stone-Houghton died from head
OL,16,Finjuries caused by her husband while
OL,17,Fhe suffered a "psychotic episode", she
OL,18,Fadded: "There was no history or any
OL,19,Findication of any risk of violence
OL,20,Fduring their loving and happy 32-year
OL,21,Frelationship."
