OL,3,CMan killed wife before taking own life
OL,4,Cduring psychotic episode, inquest hears
OL,6,F"Our parents' inquest heard evidence
OL,7,Fof clear failings, a number of which
OL,8,Fwere recognised by the coroner. In
OL,9,Flight of the coroner's findings that
OL,10,FDad had stopped taking his medication
OL,11,Fat the time of their deaths, and the
OL,12,Fevidence that steps were available to
OL,13,Fmonitor medication compliance, it is
OL,14,Fclear that more could and should have
OL,15,Fbeen done to manage the risk of Dad
OL,16,Fbecoming unwell again. The burden on
OL,17,Four family to manage this was heavy.
OL,18,FWe do not accept that this could not
OL,19,Fhave been foreseen.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
